        "title": "fix(openai-responses): bound SSE response reads via buildGuardedModelFetch",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe OpenAI Responses SDK constructor has no bounded-read wrapper on its internal `fetch` calls. A hostile or broken SSE endpoint can force the runtime to buffer an unbounded response body, creating OOM pressure. The `buildGuardedModelFetch` helper (shared 16 MiB cap, proven in #97228) needs to be wired into this path too.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/llm/providers/openai-responses.ts` — +2/-0: import `buildGuardedModelFetch` + pass it as the SDK `fetch` option\n- `src/llm/providers/openai-responses.test.ts` — +77/-0: new inline test proving the fetch wrapper is wired through the SDK constructor\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Mock-style test through the production wrapper** (mirrors #97228 `openai-completions.test.ts`):\n\n```\n$ pnpm test src/llm/providers/openai-responses.test.ts --run\n\n RUN  v4.1.8\n\n ✓ OpenAI Responses SDK client › wires buildGuardedModelFetch into the OpenAI SDK fetch option (141ms)\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  1 passed (1)\n```\n\n**Negative control**: the test asserts `expect(captured.fetch).toEqual(expect.any(Function))` and `expect(typeof captured.fetch).toBe(\"function\")` — proving the SDK receives a custom `fetch`, not the default global fetch. Without the +2 LoC in `openai-responses.ts`, the captured options would have no `fetch` key.\n\n**Cap exercised upstream**: the 16 MiB cap itself (overflow throw, byte-level counting, streaming read) is exercised in `provider-transport-fetch.test.ts` by #97228's existing tests.\n\n**Diff stats**: 2 files, +79/-0 (all non-test: +2/-0)\n\n## Verification\n\n- [x] `pnpm test src/llm/providers/openai-responses.test.ts --run` — 1 passed\n- [x] `pnpm format:fix src/llm/providers/openai-responses.ts src/llm/providers/openai-responses.test.ts` — clean\n- [x] `pnpm tsgo:core` — clean\n- [x] Branch from latest `openclaw/main` — single commit\n\nCloses #97139. Supersedes the previous `fix/sse-bounded-openai-responses` branch which accumulated re-review baggage across 6+ cycles.",
